&leth September, 1698.—— An archimandrite sent a present to the Lord Envoy of a h-uge loaf, weighing thirty pounds‚ blessed after his fashion. Another monk of high authority had added brandy‚ apples, nats, cherries‚ all preserved in spirits.

29th September, 1693.-— The Czar himself ex- amined a certain pope, an accomplice in the revolt, who, though menaced with the rack, has so far con- fesse-d nothing.
